“We don’t want to talk about Lynch courts because they show us our own ugliness,” she says.
“But I can’t build a relationship with you unless you hear me or hear what I’ve been through.”
This year’s rehearsals began in June, and on the first day almost 30 actors – a dozen whites, the rest blacks – gathered indoors and listened to a polished over the years review of the play.
