A few minutes later, Green thanks the audience, and suddenly everything is over.
The actors drop the ropes from the neck and wipe the tears.
Bradshaw embraces Marbo, a man in a suit who played the main puppet clan.
Nick Ruscona embraces the other two actors and suddenly, crying, falls into their arms: the emotional load of the performance finally fell on him.
“It’s okay,” one woman whispered.
