In Russia, there are difficulties in obtaining international driving licenses
Divisions of traffic police have a shortage of international driving licenses (IDLs).
To get such rights, you have to wait a few weeks in line, which has become a real problem for vacationers who want to go abroad on vacation in their car or rent it there.
It is worth noting that the situation with international driving licenses remains controversial.
The IDP was introduced to make it easier for foreign police to understand what is written in the national certificate, since the information in it is explained in five languages.
The requirements for international rights are recorded in the 1968 Vienna Convention on Road Traffic, but in countries that have ratified the Vienna Convention, Russian rights are recognized and so on.
However, in reality, it all depends on the specific police or rental office: some require ICU, and someone enough national rights.
To insure, drivers still receive international rights, but it should be borne in mind that in countries that have not ratified the Convention (for example, the United States, Spain, Mexico, Indonesia), the authorities have the right not to recognize either national rights or IDPs.
Now there is a problem with forms in almost all departments of traffic police, Kommersant reports, having conducted a study in a number of regions.
So, in Moscow, in the units of UGIBDD, coupons are simply not issued, forms have been missing for four months.
You can make an appointment on the website of state services, but the queue has already stretched until mid-August.
In Krasnoyarsk, it is impossible to get the Interior Ministry "for technical reasons", without going into details, in the Samara region honestly say that there are no forms, a similar situation is developing in other cities.
Many Muscovites have already faced the problem, such messages are increasingly appearing in social networks:
Irina Burmistrova: "Guess why you can't get international rights in Moscow?"
That's right, because all the police departments ran out of forms.
Elena Podkolzina: "A question to knowledgeable people!"
We need to get international rights urgently.
In Moscow, all the time is hammered far ahead, on the spot, coupons are not issued at all (there is a button, but the coupon can not be given).
It seems that the portal of public services shows that in St. Petersburg free time to hell.
Has anyone tried it in another city?
Will it work?
As explained in the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation, the requirements for forms of international driving licenses have changed, so new forms are delivered to the departments of the State Automobile Inspection.
This may be associated with a deficit, however, it is unclear what changes we are talking about, this was not previously reported.
The forms are purchased by the Special Purpose Center in the field of road safety (CSN BDD) of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation and then supplied to traffic police units.
In recent years, all contracts were concluded with JSC "Goznak": in 2014-2015, almost 200,000 forms of the Ministry of Internal Affairs were produced, in 2016 15,000 forms were purchased, in 2017 - 90,000, but the last contract was concluded on July 18 with LLC "First Printed Yard" for the production of 70,000 forms.
There is a version that the CSN simply did not have time to hold the tender, which is why there was a deficit.
However, there are other versions of the lack of forms: because of the crisis, many people began to travel independently not to Europe, but to cheaper Asian countries - China, Thailand and so on.
What rights are accepted there, it is unclear, so people are reinsured, and therefore there was an excitement demand for international "crusts".
Recently it became known that professional drivers will have to pass an exam to confirm their qualifications.
This proposal was made by the Ministry of Transport.
The International Driving Permit (IDP) of the new model is valid from May 31, 2011.
