What remains is insufficient to implement the modernization plan.
"It is problematic to get money from the owner, it is difficult to talk about attracting borrowed funds from large credit organizations," Deputy Head of the Ministry of Agriculture of Crimea Sergey Petelin said in April this year.
The Parliament of Crimea included the company in the forecast privatization plan for 2017.
It was proposed to hold its shares and put them up for auction.
