In Russia, two new territories of advanced socio-economic development will appear - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city, where there are 15,000 people, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment in the city, as well as create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities under which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, includes crop production, animal husbandry, production of food products, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of LLC "Abakansky mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, a territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the monotown, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC "Ural Steel", as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities under which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monotowns of the Orenburg region to receive the status of TOR.
The territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment to improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of TOR can be distinguished the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free zone regime, preferential mode of connection to various infrastructure objects, as well as preferential rates on rent.
